		<div id="post_message_1208128">
                  
                  Ok, before I start explaining, let me show you two comparisons. It should be pretty obvious, especially after the second one, what I am going to say.<br />
<br />
<b><a href="http://vg.curse.com/database/items/details/1349398/" target="_blank">Pantaloons of Chaos</a><br />
Light Armor<br />
149 Armor Class<br />
+19 Vitality<br />
+37 Intelligence<br />
+9 Wisdom<br />
+114 Energy<br />
+89 Spell Damage<br />
Item Level: 47</b><br />
<br />
vs.<br />
<br />
<b><a href="http://vg.curse.com/database/items/details/1401513/" target="_blank">Hegnerian's Leggings of Incineration</a><br />
Light Armor<br />
149 Armor Class<br />
+5 Vitality<br />
+37 Intelligence<br />
+14 Wisdom<br />
+74 Fire Damage Focus<br />
+84 Spell Damage<br />
+63 Critical Spell Hit Chance<br />
Item Level: 47</b><br />
<br />
<br />
And....<br />
<br />
<b><a href="http://vg.curse.com/database/items/details/1350959/" target="_blank">Phytotoxinous Cuffs</a><br />
54 Armor Class<br />
+7 Intelligence<br />
+7 Wisdom<br />
+81 Hit Points<br />
+81 Energy<br />
Item Level: 45</b><br />
<br />
vs.<br />
<br />
<b><a href="http://vg.curse.com/database/items/details/622558/" target="_blank">Infused Infineum Bracers</a><br />
28 Armor Class<br />
+5 Vitality<br />
+5 Intelligence<br />
+19 Spirit Resistance<br />
+6 Spell Damage Focus<br />
Item Level: 25</b><br />
<br />
I will get right to the point. Health/Energy is using way too many itemization points. Sure more health and energy is nice, but at the cost of that many stats is insane.<br />
<br />
I just linked 25 yellow vs a 45 heroic. The 25 yellow had 4 less stats, but 6 SDF, and +19 spirit resistance.<br />
<br />
On another note, just a personal pet peeve of mine, look at the heg vs chaos pants. Same level, almost identical stats, almost identical spell damage rating, but heg has +74 FDR and +63 crit. <br />
<br />
74 FDR and 63 crit = 14 vit, -5 wis, +5 SDR, and +114 energy?<br />
<br />
Errr, again. Energy taking up WAY too many points.<br />
<br />
Now, for the proposed part.<br />
<br />
Decreased the itemization cost of both health and energy.<br />
<br />
Then decrease energy even MORE.<br />
<br />
The health on armor is nice, but it still is using too much.<br />
<br />
The energy on armor is useless, and needs to cost **VERY LITTLE**.
                  
		</div>
