                  If you don't mind me sticking it in here - I suppose it's tangentially related to the subject at hand - I think the stats for some of the upgraded Swamp armors are a little off. My specific example is the Flordiel legs - you actually have less +spell damage in the upgraded (heroic) version than in the non-upgraded (rare) version (along with more INT and SDF, and less WIS and HP). I guess I'm not sure why the stat distribution would be that drastically different on the upgraded version - especially when the pure +spell damage is the biggest draw on the item, so you're basically taking a downgrade by &quot;upgrading&quot; it. Please and thank you, as always. <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" /><br />
