		<div id="post_message_1208912">
                  
                  Yes<br />
<br />
7mana= 1wis on item budget<br />
<br />
but for a sorcerer 1wis = 16 Mana at lvl50<br />
Emilia 518 wis = 8015 Mana<br />
Emilia 509 wis = 7871 Mana<br />
<br />
So actually mana is &quot;overpriced&quot; for us.<br />
I expect this to be the oposite for Constitution.<br />
<br />
Emilia 69 Con = 2551 hp<br />
Emilia 74 Con = 2570 hp<br />
<br />
So 1 Con = 3.8<br />
<br />
<br />
What does this mean ?   The Hp/Sta Mana/Wis formula is NOT &quot;generic&quot;.<br />
<br />
Thus if you are a caster looking for manapool stay away from +Mana.<br />
You will pay TWO times as much for the same amount of mana.<br />
<br />
And if you are looking for hit points, stay away from +Stamina.<br />
You will get HALF the stats for +Sta than you would from pure +Hp.<br />
<br />
<br />
I really dislike this, it should be the &quot;same&quot; for everyone.<br />
Because a 20sta 100hp ring will be more &quot;Tank&quot; oriented than a 240hp ring.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
