		<div id="post_message_1212536">
                  
                  i want to keep this discussion going<br />
<br />
let say you were designing an item and wanted to put a total value of 336 energy.<br />
<br />
If you put +336 energy you consumed about 42 stat points.<br />
If you put +21 wisdom you consumed only 21 stat points.<br />
<br />
Comparing an item like<br />
<br />
lvl 41 T4 UR hexes robe<br />
41 int<br />
21 wis <br />
110 sdf.<br />
<br />
if it had +336 energy the remaining item points would only have 20 points left for distribution.  so you could end up with something like this<br />
<br />
20 int<br />
+336 energy<br />
110 sdf.<br />
<br />
<br />
as you can see comparing the two robes, the +41 int / 21 wis is far superior, but both items use the SAME amount of item points.<br />
<br />
This is the REAL issue here, and imho needs to be fixed.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
