	<td class="alt1" id="td_post_1212674">
	
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1212674">
                  
                  <div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Cylus</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">Now, let's say that you reach the WIS cap during every raid.  Wouldn't energy then become more important or is energy regen just so high that it doesn't matter?  Keep in mind that, with APW, many people will begin reaching the stat caps, at least with their primary attributes (STR, INT, etc).<br />
 <br />
To be clear, I'm not defending or bashing the system, I'm merely relating one of the thoughts that went into the system, afaik (most of it was all done before my time, hehe).</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
I hadn't considered capping wisdom, but after some thought here's why I dont think it will happen soon.<br />
<br />
currently cylus there are only 3 archtype's that can buff wisdom.<br />
Healer:<br />
#1 bloodmage +64 wis<br />
#2 cleric +40 wis<br />
(since they are the same archtype they dont stack)<br />
<br />
Caster:<br />
#3 Psi +84 wis<br />
#4 Necro's +45ish (in combat 60s buff that can be maintained as long as in combat)<br />
<br />
Offensive fighter<br />
#5 bard +40ish<br />
Defensive fighter<br />
0<br />
<br />
what we end up totaling is +233 Wisdom from buffs if you have bm psi necro in your raid / group.<br />
<br />
I'm a High elf, highest base WIS of all the classes.  I can put + wisdom on every slot, and with it cap out around 600 wis, but sacrifice a LOT of int to do so.<br />
<br />
out of combat i'll have 790 wisdom buffed by psi/bm/bard<br />
in combat with psi/bm/necro/bard i'll cap out at 833 or around 800 points.  some 100 points shy, with still taking a large loss in +spell crit +spell damage rating and +int.<br />
<br />
Even if we bump that up to 850 and be conservative, that means a full set of APW armor will have over 50 wisdom to cap it out with a group/raid built around maxing it.<br />
<br />
<br />
Now thats taking it to the extreme, for a FULL +wisdom build, which lets be honest isn't the dps caster archtypes focus.<br />
<br />
<br />
How about looking at my build.<br />
<br />
currently sitting at 644 int and 500 wis self buffed.<br />
<br />
that puts me at 750 wis with the above 4 mentioned classes, and APW gear will need to have 150 more points of wisdom on the gear before I cap out on wisdom.<br />
<br />
<br />
The point I was trying to make in my previous post, was that you dont have to pile all the points on just wisdom.  The &quot;extra&quot; points left over could be re-distributed into other stats, like int, SDR, SCR, SDF, vit....ect, and end up making an item that is a bit more balanced.<br />
<br />
Is it possible to make +hp/energy on items have a *base* value for each tier?<br />
<br />
something like <br />
1-9 items have a base +5hp/energy <br />
10-19 have +10<br />
20-29 have +20<br />
30-39 have +30<br />
40-49 have +40<br />
50 + have +50<br />
<br />
You could even break it down by Item quality (common - legendary)<br />
and by Archtype (DEF fighter - healer - caster - OFF fighter)<br />
<br />
kind of like AC scales currently.<br />
<br />
That way +hp / energy wont detract from an Items &quot;points&quot; and if you wanted to add &quot;more&quot; you can use some of the items points to increase said amount.<br />
<br />
For example armor of the same lvl and quality dont all have the same A/C value, some items have more a/c than others.  not talking about + mit bonus stuff on items either just the base a/c.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Energy regen part:<br />
Energy regen is pretty crazy in this game, it gets tossed out like candy.  Especially with crafted items allowing you to get almost as much as a hyatet shaman or psi can provide via buffs.<br />
<br />
Thats NOT counting energy regenerating abilities, like GE, and our shard. All of the healer/caster archtypes have at least 1 way to regain energy during combat.<br />
<br />
To show an example<br />
when I play my g/f shaman, she has 0 items with energy regen on them, and can be an effective healer indefinately with 4K energy.<br />
<br />
When i play my sorc, with a hyatets + 117 energy regen buff + firebarrier 3 I can nuke almost indefinately with Cv2.  If I use CV4 i can maintain that for well past 4 min straight with about 8k energy (500 wis) which gives me plenty of time to use GE to get back to full.  Or use my racial ability, or use a charge on the druid energy regen berry.<br />
<br />
Except for druids who have horrid power issues, I dont see many other classes with decent gear going oop unless they get sloppy or lazy.
                  
		</div>
