		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1216628">
                  
                  I understand the concept behind having the ratio's that are in place, but there are several factors which seem unbalanced to me.  I've mentioned before the fact that instruments mod's are costing too much and are severaly limiting the impact of stats on instruments.  As a result, we end up with mods our own level and no stats, or stats and a mod equal to the one we had 20 levels prior.  <br />
<br />
The same holds true with +crit / +focus / + energy.   These all have very low values and as a result you can get excessive amounts.  An example would be the Luclin Jewelry.  Here we have items which give 2-3% crit worth of +crit rating or evasion.  2-3% crit in terms of Dexterity is about 150 Dex.  2-3% evasion is the equivelant of 200 Dex for bards.  Yet add a few HP to the item and the crit is reduced in half.  <br />
<br />
I'm all for the reduction of values on Hit Points, Energy, Resists and Instrument Mods and the increase in value on +DF/SDF.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
